Plug-in name: RteGen
Plug-in shortname: rte
Description: generates annotations for runtime error checking

Most options of the form '-rte-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-rte-no-option-name'.

Most options of the form '-option-name' and without any parameter
have an opposite with the name '-no-option-name'.

Options taking a string as argument should preferably be written
-option-name="argument".

***** LIST OF AVAILABLE OPTIONS:

-rte                when on (off by default), generates annotations for
                    runtime error checking (opposite option is -no-rte)
-rte-div            when on (default), annotate for modulo and division by
                    zero (set by default, opposite option is -rte-no-div)
-rte-float-to-int   when on (default), annotate casts from floating-point to
                    integer (set by default, opposite option is
                    -rte-no-float-to-int)
-rte-initialized <fct>  for each function in 'fct', annotates reads of non
                    struct or union values from local variables and pointers
                    with initialization tests, see documentation for more
                    details (preferably use -rte-initialized="fct")
-rte-mem            when on (default), annotate for valid pointer or array
                    access (set by default, opposite option is -rte-no-mem)
-rte-pointer-call   when on, annotate functions calls through pointers (set
                    by default, opposite option is -rte-no-pointer-call)
-rte-select <fun>   select <fun> for analysis (default all functions)
                    (preferably use -rte-select="fun")
-rte-shift          when on (default), annotate for left and right shifts by
                    a value out of bounds (set by default, opposite option is
                    -rte-no-shift)
-rte-trivial-annotations  generate all annotations even if they trivially
                    hold (from evaluation of constant expressions,
                    syntactical rules...) (opposite option is
                    -rte-no-trivial-annotations)
-rte-use-eva-results  When enabled, do not emit annotations on functions
                    analyzed by Eva (set by default, opposite option is
                    -rte-no-use-eva-results)
-rte-warn           when on (default), emits warning on broken asserts (set
                    by default, opposite option is -rte-no-warn)

*** DEBUG

-rte-debug <n>      level of debug for plug-in RteGen (default to 0)

*** GETTING INFORMATION

-rte-help           help of plug-in RteGen
-rte-h              alias for option -rte-help

*** OUTPUT MESSAGES

-rte-log <K_1:file_1,...>  copy log messages from RteGen to a file. <K> is a
                    combination of these characters:
                    a: ALL messages (equivalent to 'dfiruw')
                    d: debug       e: user or internal error (same as 'iu')
                    f: feedback    i: internal error
                    r: result      u: user error    w: warning
                    An empty <K> (e.g. ":file.txt") defaults to 'iruw'. One
                    plug-in can output to several files and vice-versa.
                    (preferably use -rte-log="K_1:file_1,...")
-rte-msg-key <k1[,...,kn]>  enables message display for categories
                    <k1>,...,<kn>. Use -rte-msg-key help to get a list of
                    available categories, and * to enable all categories
                    (preferably use -rte-msg-key="k1[,...,kn]")
-rte-verbose <n>    level of verbosity for plug-in RteGen (default to 1)
-rte-warn-key <k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]>  set warning status for category <k1>
                    to <s1>,...,<kn> to <sn>. Use -rte-warn-key help to get a
                    list of available categories, and * to enable all
                    categories. Possible statuses are inactive, feedback,
                    warning, error, abort, feedback-once, warning-once,
                    error-once. Defaults to warning. (preferably use
                    -rte-warn-key="k1[=s1][,...,kn[=sn]]")
